Serves 4Ingredients:500g fish fillets, eg salmon or hake15ml (1 tbsp) finely chopped fresh chives15ml (1 tbsp) finely chopped fresh parsley15ml (1 tbsp) finely chopped fresh dill1 garlic clove, chopped, optionalZest of one lemon10ml (2 tsp) lemon juice5ml (1 tsp) Dijon mustard15ml (1 tbsp) mayonnaise125ml ( cup) coconut or almond flour, plus extra for coatingSalt and pepperOil, for fryingTo serve:Blanched green vegetables (such as peas, asparagus and green beans) and baby lettuce leaves30-45ml (2-3 tbsp) vinaigrette dressingTonight's supper: Low-carb chorizo & cabbage pieMethod:1) Cut the fish into blocks and combine with the herbs, garlic, lemon zest, juice, mustard and mayonnaise in the bowl of a food processor. Blend using the pulse button, taking care not to overmix to a pulp. Add the flour and pulse again. Season.2) With wet hands, divide the mixture into 4 or 8 portions and shape into fishcakes. Coat in extra coconut or almond flour.3) In a frying pan, heat 2-3cm of oil and fry the fishcakes for about 3-5 minutes on each side, turning carefully. Serve with a salad of blanched green vegetables tossed with vinaigrette.